thermus mediatlanticus</em> sp. nov.</s></p><p class="etymology"><s><em>Vulcanithermus mediatlanticus</em> (me.di.at.lan′ti.cus. L. adj. <em>medius</em> middle; L. masc. adj. <em>atlanticus</em> Atlantic; N.L. adj. <em>mediatlanticus</em> from the middle of the Atlantic).</s></p><p class="description"><s>Displays the following properties in addition to those given in the genus description.</s><s>Optimal growth temperature is 70 °C.</s><s>The optimal pH is around 6·7.</s><s>The optimum salinity is 3 % NaCl.</s><s>The chemical composition of the species is identical to that of the genus.</s><s>The G+C content of the DNA of the type strain is 68·4 mol%.</s><s>The type strain, TR<sup>T</sup> (=DSM 14978<sup>T</sup> =VKM B-2292<sup>T</sup> =JCM 11956<sup>T</sup>), was isolated from the Rainbow deep-sea hydrothermal vent field on the Mid-Atlantic Ridge.</s></p></content></protolog>